title: For Sale/Trade:  1935 Tula CN Mosin Nagant PE sniper.
location: Rapid City, South Dakota, United States
postcontent: 1935 CN marked Tula PE sniper.  This rifle was originally a PE sniper.  These rifles were decommissioned during refurbishment in the 50s and turned into standard rifles.  Scope holes were plugged and straight bolt handles installed.  This rifle was "resnipered" back to sniper configuration here stateside.  Base, scope mount, and PE scope are reproduction built in Ukraine on the same tooling and machines the originals were made and are no longer available.  These are among the best reproduction scopes available.  Reticle moves during adjustment just like originals.  Original configured PE snipers go for extreme amounts of money.  There are only a handful of all original PE snipers still alive.  Most are in museums overseas.  This is the next best thing.Text 760-221-3822
